<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="over-prep">over <strong><em>prep</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'əʊvə(r)/    美 /'oʊvər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[表示高于 / 大于]：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>在…上方 (未触及) 【反:under】：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The moon rose over the hills, and the stars appeared in the sky.
月亮从山坡上升起，天空中出现了点点繁星。</p><footer>2012 四川改</footer></div>

<h3 id="above-on-over">辨析 above, on, over</h3>
<p>三者都含有“在…上”之意。<br />
<strong>above</strong> 表示“在…上方 (未必在正上方)”，与 below相对，两者不接触。
<strong>on</strong> 表示“在…上”，两者接触，与beneath相对。
<strong>over</strong> 表示“在…正上方”，两者不接触，与 under相对。</p>
<ul>
<li>覆盖在…的上面 【反:under】；遍布在…的上面：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>spread a cloth over the table
把桌布铺在桌上</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(数目、程度方面) 超过 【反:under】：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The headmaster is over 50.
校长五十开外。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The speech lasted over an hour.
演讲持续了一个多小时。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(在地位、职权、势力等方面) 在…之上：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He ruled over a great empire.
他统治着一个伟大的帝国。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is over me in the office.
他的职务比我高。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[表示在空间或时间上从一点到另一点]：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>越过；穿过：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The dog jumped over some bushes and saw the little stream.
狗跳过灌木丛看到了小溪。</p><footer>2012 陕西</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There’s a bus stop just over the road.
路对面就有一个公共汽车站。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>通过; 凭借：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I booked my train ticket over the phone / Internet.
我通过电话 / 在网上订了火车票。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>在…期间：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Shakespeare’s play Hamlet has been made into at least ten different films over the past years.
在过去这些年中，莎士比亚的戏剧《哈姆雷特》至少被翻拍成10部不同的电影。</p><footer>2013 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In Britain, it’s not unusual to have a business meeting over breakfast.
在英国，边吃早餐边开商务会议并不稀奇。</p><footer>2012 安徽</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>度过…阶段：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The Greek government can’t <strong>get over</strong> the present difficulties unless it gets more financial support.
除非得到更多的财政援助，否则希腊政府不可能度过目前的困境。</p><footer>2012 福建</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>关于；由于：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an argument over money
有关金钱问题的争论</p></div>

<p>注: over常与感情动词cry, weep, laugh, mourn, sigh 等连用，表示原因。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He would laugh the loudest over fun and be the saddest over anyone’s misfortune.
他会因为有趣的事而放声大笑，也会为任何人的不幸而极度悲伤。</p><footer>2017 全国</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="all-over">all over</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>到处；各处：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Countries all over the world name places in similar ways.
全世界的国家都用相似的方式给地方命名。</p><footer>2009 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He made speeches all over the USA about his experiences.
他在美国各地发表演说讲述自己的经历。</p><footer>北师大① – 2</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I’m sorry I didn’t phone you, but I’ve been very busy <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the past couple of weeks.  （2011 山东改）  </li>
<li>You can’t wear a blue jacket <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ that shirt — it’ll look terrible.  </li>
<li>They had a pleasant chat <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ a cup of coffee.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. over  2. over  3. over  </p></div>